= 808 | blank_name = GNIS feature ID | blank_info = 2583416 | footnotes = | name = | pop_est_as_of = | pop_est_footnotes = | population_est = }} East Honolulu is a census-designated place (CDP) in Honolulu County, Hawaii, United States. As of 2020, the CDP had a population of 50,922 people. == Geography == The United States Census Bureau says that the CDP has an area of 34 mi (89 km) and 33% of the area is water. The CDP is located on Oahu. The CDP starts directly east of the center of Honolulu, and ends at Makapu'u Point (which is the easternmost point on the island). == Demographics == There are many races present in the CDP. * Asian 47.2% (24,021) * White 23.4% (11,926) * Mixed 20.2% (10,305) * Hispanic 5.4% (2,767) * Native Hawaiians or other Pacific Islanders 2.8% (1,441) * Black 0.5% (278) * Other races 0.4% (184) As of 2022, the median income that households make in East Honolulu is about $151,224 USD. 48.9% is males and 51.1% are female. The median age in the CDP is 50 years old. == References == == Other websites == *East Honolulu on City-Data Category:Census-designated places in Hawaii
